  "prompt": "It goes without saying that money laundering is illegal, doesn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, it goes without saying that money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. Money laundering is the process of making illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. This practice is criminalized because it enables illegal activities to thrive, undermines financial systems, and harms economies.\n\nLaws against money laundering are enforced rigorously, and penalties for those convicted can include hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment. Additionally, financial institutions and businesses are required to implement anti-money laundering (AML) measures to detect and report suspicious activities.",
